g.text: Traffic manager
UC301 - Import data from countries, ports, borders and seadists from the database to build a freight network.
UC302 - Colour the map using as few colours as possible
UC303 - Know which places are closest to all other places
Ship Captain
UC304 - Have access to audit trails for a given container of a given cargo manifest
Port Manager
UC306 - Know the occupancy rate of each warehouse and an estimate of the containers leaving the warehouse during the next 30 days
UC310 - Intend to have a map of the occupation of the existing resources in the port during a given month
Client
UC312 - Know the current situation of a specific container being used to transport my goods
Port Staff
UC313 - Fill a statically reserved matrix in memory with each container's ID in its respective place
UC314 - Know the total number of free/occupied slots in the transport vehicle
UC315 - Know if a container is there or not
UC316 - Know the total number of occupied slots
Ship Chief Electrical Engineer
UC317 - Know what set of materials to use in a container, to operate at temperatures of 7°C
UC318 - Know what set of materials to use in a container, to operate at temperatures of -5 °C
UC319 - Know the thermal resistance, for each operating temperature, of each container that must contain at least three different materials in its walls
UC320 - Intend to present in a summary document, the choice of materials considered for the two types of containers considered, and their thermal resistances
